Stroma is the foundation layer of a larger system. The trust network is substrate, not product.

## Core Insight

Stroma's architecture (identity masking, `/propose` governance, Freenet contracts, trust topology, federation) serves double duty: trust management for Signal groups AND the foundation for trust-gated collective intelligence (MutualAI convergence).

Nothing in Stroma needs to change to support this. The architecture was already right.

